list.abstract: 胜利航运(SENATOR)由塞奇(Karl-Heinz Sager)创立于1994年，总部位于德国不来梅，是由罗斯托克航运和不来梅航运合并而来的。1994年，胜利航运(SENATOR)与DSR合并。新成立的DSR Senator成为了德国最大的船东，拥有50艘集装箱船，总运力达80,000 TEU，并拥有15,000个自有集装箱。1994年，DSR Senator共承运了67万TEU货量，营业额达到了10亿美元。当时，DSR Senator的股权分配情况为，DSR持有50%，Bremer Vulkan持有45%，余下的5%属于Commerzbank银行。1996年，由于业务铺得太广，Bremer Vulkan宣告破产。1997年，韩进海运(HANJIN)买下了胜利航运(SENATOR)80%的股份。保留下来的小股东则有Reederei Laeisz,当时经营着胜利航运(SENATOR)旗下33艘船中的12艘；BIG投资公司，隶属于不来梅市。韩进海运(HANJIN)与胜利航运(SENATOR)的运力总合在当时排在世界第4位。然而，仅仅11年过后，胜利航运(SENATOR)这家在成立之初就不以盈利为唯一目的公司就退出了历史舞台。

yingyinNormal.en: Sir? Senator Sheer. Senator, you did a fine job.
yingyinNormal.zh: 先生？希尔参议员。参议员，你干得太漂亮了。

yingyinNormal.en: In return for what? You convince the senator to pull out.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你要什么回报？你说服参议员退出。

yingyinNormal.en: You can show the senator out now, thank you. Yes, sir.
yingyinNormal.zh: 可以送参议员出去了，谢谢。是，先生。

yingyinNormal.en: You won't win, Senator. We both know that. But I can't help her.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你赢不了的，参议员，你我都清楚。可我不能帮她。

yingyinNormal.en: Senator Dean Austen of Ohio, the leadership's top choice for running mate.
yingyinNormal.zh: 俄亥俄参议员，迪恩·奥斯汀，领导层竞选伙伴的首选。

yingyinNormal.en: But let's put that aside for a moment and talk about your good friend. Who? Senator Austen.
yingyinNormal.zh: 先不谈那个，来说说你的好朋友。谁？奥斯汀参议员。

yingyinNormal.en: Samaritan has preempted multiple threats to national security. You're welcome, Senator.
yingyinNormal.zh: 撒马利亚人预先解除了多起对国家安全的威胁。不用谢，参议员。

yingyinNormal.en: No luck with Leahy or Durbin? They're endorsing Hillary. We could go with a state senator.
yingyinNormal.zh: 莱希和德宾拉拢不过来吗？他们支持希拉里，我们可以找一位州参议员。

yingyinNormal.en: Senator. I'm honored, Mr. President. I just have one major reservation. Claire. Yes, sir.
yingyinNormal.zh: 参议员。我很荣幸，总统先生，我只有一个很大的顾虑。克莱尔。是的，先生。

yingyinNormal.en: I wonder if our fine senator has become more of a problem than asset. One that needs to be eliminated.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我想知道这位，好参议员，是不是已经从资产变成了负担，需要加以清理。

yingyinNormal.en: Was it? I have as many delegates as you do, Senator. But if you start pushing yours my way... You double.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是吗？支持我的党代表不比你少，参议员，但如果你开始支持我…你得票翻倍。

yingyinNormal.en: Donald. Don't do it. Claire. I know what you and Senator Mitchell were planning. Do what you were supposed to do.
yingyinNormal.zh: 唐纳德，别这么做，克莱尔。我知道你和米切尔参议员在谋划什么。做你本该做的事。

yingyinNormal.en: We had a deal, Senator. We get the feeds. You get the relevant numbers. What we do with that information is entirely up to us.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们约定好了，参议员，我们拿到信号，你们拿到相关号码，用那些信息做什么，完全是我们自己的事。

yingyinNormal.en: Lawyer, senator, CEO, scientist, physicist, winners of Nobel and Pulitzer Prizes, or late night talk show host.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们可能成为律师，参议员，首席执行官，科学家，物理学家，诺贝尔奖及普利策奖得主，乃至深夜谈话节目主持人。

yingyinNormal.en: Are you, as a United States senator, personally comfortable saying to a grieving parent, Superman could have saved your child, but on principle, we did not want him to act?
yingyinNormal.zh: 而你，作为一名美国参议员，能否很坦然地对沉浸在悲痛中的父母说“超人本可以救你的孩子，但原则上来说，我们不希望他去救？”

yingyinNormal.en: I'm glad you brought up nepotism, Senator.
yingyinNormal.zh: 正好你提到任人唯亲，议员先生。

yingyinNormal.en: Do you know the oldest lie in America, senator? Can I call you June?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你知道美国最古老的谎言吗，议员？我能称呼你朱恩吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Senator. My dad always said that Kentucky mash was the secret to health.
yingyinNormal.zh: 议员，我爸爸过去常说肯塔基的麦芽浆是永葆健康的秘诀。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, thank you for calling me back, Senator. No problem, Peter. I got to keep my golfing buddy happy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 谢谢你打回给我，议员。没事，彼得，我得让我的高尔夫球友高兴啊。
